    "comment": "Rationale: Quantitative immunogold reactivity against SNX1 in mouse hippocampal pyramidal neurons shows a predominant postsynaptic distribution. SNX1 is localized to endosome membranes, but the subclass of endosome (early/late/recycling) is not unambiguously determined. Experimental description: our wild-type eight-week-old male C57BL/6N mice were perfused transcardially with 4% paraformaldehyde/0.1 M sodium phosphate buffer (PB, pH 7.2) for light microscopic immuno- histochemistry or with 4% paraformaldehyde/0.1% glutaraldehyde/ 0.1 M PB for immunoelectron microscopy.",
